<CSSConditionRule>
<summary>
An object implementing the <strong><c>CSSConditionRule</c></strong> interface represents a single condition CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_syntax/At-rule">at-rule</see>, which consists of a condition and a statement block.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>Three objects derive from <c>CSSConditionRule</c>: <see cref="CSSMediaRule"/>, <see cref="CSSContainerRule"/> and <see cref="CSSSupportsRule"/>.</para><para></para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSS_Object_Model/Using_dynamic_styling_information">Using dynamic styling information</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSSConditionRule"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSConditionRule>
<CSSConditionRuleConditionText>
<summary>
The read-only <strong><c>conditionText</c></strong> property of<br/>the <see cref="CSSConditionRule"/> interface returns or sets the text of the CSS<br/>rule.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSS_Object_Model/Using_dynamic_styling_information">Using dynamic styling information</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSSConditionRule/conditionText"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
</CSSConditionRuleConditionText>
